From: Mark Kretschmann <kretschmann@kde.org>
Subject: [PATCH] Patch for crash on startup with Info applet
 Since Amarok 2.3.0 had been released we were struggling with one very
 bizarre bug, a crash on startup induced by the "Info" applet. As it
 turns out, this is really a bug in Qt, and it will be fixed in Qt
 4.6.3.
 .
 However, we were able to make a simple workaround that fixes the issue
 directly in Amarok, and this workaround does not have any side
 effects. Some of you packagers have asked us for this patch, so I'm
 attaching it here to this mail. You could either decide to patch Qt,
 or Amarok, or maybe both (the crash might also affect other Plasma
 applets). But I would personally recommend patching Amarok in any
 case, as this is just safer.
Bug: https://bugs.kde.org/show_bug.cgi?id=227639
Bug: https://bugs.kde.org/show_bug.cgi?id=229756
Origin: upstream

Signed-off-by: Modestas Vainius <modestas@vainius.eu>

---
